  "reasoning": "First, compute the probability that the sum of three card draws with replacement is a multiple of 10. The distribution of point values: P(i) = 1/13 for i = 1,...,9 and P(10) = 4/13. Using convolution or generating functions, the probability that the sum mod 10 is 0 is 244/2197. Since gcd(244, 2197) = 1, this fraction is in lowest terms, so m = 244, n = 2197. The problem then defines d as the gcd of the numerator and denominator of this probability fraction, so d = 1. Thus k = d + 0 = 1.\n\nNext, find the polynomial P(x) satisfying P(1) = 1 and P(2x)/P(x+1) = 8 - 56/(x+7). Simplify the equation to P(2x)/P(x+1) = 8x/(x+7). Assuming P is a polynomial, comparing degrees gives deg(P) = 3. Let P(x) = ax^3 + bx^2 + cx + d. Substitute into the equation and equate coefficients to find b = 8a, c = 12a, d = 0, so P(x) = ax(x+2)(x+6). Using P(1) = 1 gives a = 1/21. Then P(-1) = (-1)(1)(5)/21 = -5/21.",
